espeak
------------------------------------------
eSpeak is a compact open source software speech synthesizer for English 
and other languages, for Linux and Windows. eSpeak produces good quality 
English speech. It uses a different synthesis method from other open 
source TTS engines, and sounds quite different.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-1.7.1-1
  libgcc1-4.3.4-3
  libportaudio2-19.20071207-10

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.19.51-1
  cygport-0.9.80-1
  gcc4-core-4.3.4-3
  gcc4-g++-4.3.4-3
  make-3.81-2

Canonical website:
  http://espeak.sourceforge.net/

Canonical download:
  http://downloads.sourceforge.net/espeak/

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  unpack espeak-1.43-X-src.tar.bz2
    if you use setup to install this src package, it will be
	 unpacked under /usr/src automatically
  cd /usr/src
  cygport ./espeak-1.43-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/espeak-1.43-X-src.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/espeak-1.43-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libespeak-devel-1.43-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libespeak1-1.43-X.tar.bz2

-------------------------------------------

